---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Layout & Courtyard Flow | Ellamin Courtyard Retreat" description="Understand the inferred guest flow across the pool, house frontage, gazebo, pergola, BBQ bay, lawn, parking, and interior placeholder zones.">
  <section class="v3-band pb-12">
    <div class="v3-container">
      <div class="v3-split">
        <div>
          <p class="v3-eyebrow">Compound layout</p>
          <h1 class="v3-section-title mt-3 font-display">One courtyard, several clear zones.</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[1.02rem] leading-8 text-[color:var(--muted)]">
          This layout is inferred from the exterior photos. It is a guest-facing mockup, not an architectural plan. It makes the decision easier by showing where guests gather, swim, eat, park, and enter the house.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 v3-photo-grid">
        <figure class="v3-media-frame aspect-[16/10]">
          <img class="v3-theme-day" src="/images/ellamin-courtyard-day-main.webp" alt="Daytime view showing Ellamin Courtyard pool, lawn, pergola, gazebo, and BBQ bay" loading="eager" />
          <img class="v3-theme-night" src="/images/ellamin-courtyard-night-front.webp" alt="Night view showing Ellamin Courtyard house frontage, pool, pergola, and lit pathway" loading="eager" />
          <figcaption class="v3-media-label">Main orientation: pool at front-left, house and porch center, BBQ bay right</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <figure class="v3-media-frame min-h-[220px]">
            <img src="/images/ellamin-courtyard-family-day.webp" alt="Family day use of lawn, pool, and shaded dining areas" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption class="v3-media-label">Family-day flow: adults can gather while children swim under supervision</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="v3-media-frame min-h-[220px]">
            <img src="/images/ellamin-courtyard-rain-sunset.webp" alt="Rain and sunset view of the pool and covered dining zone" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption class="v3-media-label">Covered zones stay useful during rain or evening use</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-20">
    <div class="v3-container">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-12">
        <div class="lg:col-span-4">
          <p class="v3-eyebrow">Inferred zone map</p>
          <h2 class="v3-section-title mt-3 font-display">How the space works.</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-[color:var(--muted)]">
            The page should communicate spatial logic before guests ask the host. Interior rooms remain placeholder until real interior photos are available.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-8">
          <div class="v3-zone-map">
            <div class="v3-zone v3-zone-pool">
              <p class="v3-eyebrow">Wet zone</p>
              <strong>Private pool and deck</strong>
              <p>Primary emotional anchor. Best shown with day and night photos because the mood changes materially.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="v3-zone-column">
              <div class="v3-zone">
                <strong>House frontage</strong>
                <p>Entry porch, sliding doors, and covered transition between indoor rest and outdoor gathering.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="v3-zone">
                <strong>Pergola and lawn</strong>
                <p>Dry social zone for seated adults, children nearby, and photo-friendly family day setup.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="v3-zone">
                <strong>Gazebo and BBQ bay</strong>
                <p>Food prep, shaded dining, charcoal grill, and practical event staging along the right edge.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="v3-zone">
                <strong>Interior placeholder</strong>
                <p>Two bedrooms, bathrooms, living, and kitchen should be replaced with real interior proof later.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-24">
    <div class="v3-container">
      <div class="v3-logistics">
        <article class="v3-card">
          <strong>Vehicle planning</strong>
          <p>Keep one host-confirmed parking fact visible, then explain overflow/visitor parking only after it is verified.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="v3-card">
          <strong>Supervision sightline</strong>
          <p>The photos show adults can sit in shaded areas while keeping the pool and lawn within view.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="v3-card">
          <strong>Rain and night readiness</strong>
          <p>Evening/rain photos prove the covered dining bay and warm pool lighting are not just daytime promises.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
